@startuml
title 6. Full Workflow: Feature Lifecycle
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor Student as S
participant "GitWizard" as W
actor Teammate as T

== Option 1: Start Feature ==

S -> W : Option 1
W -> S : Show open issues
S -> W : Pick issue #2
W -> W : Create branch\nfeature/BR-02-edit-existing-community
W -> S : "Branch created! Go to IDE."

note over S : Implement feature\nand write tests

== Option 2: Save Progress (repeat) ==

S -> W : Option 2
W -> W : mvn clean verify
W -> S : "Build successful!"
S -> W : Message + issue #2
W -> W : git commit
W -> S : "Committed!"

note over S : Continue working...\nRepeat option 2

== Option 3: Submit for Review ==

S -> W : Option 3
W -> W : git push + gh pr create
W -> S : "PR #35 created!"

S -> T : "Please review"
T -> T : Review and approve

== Option 4: Merge & Cleanup ==

S -> W : Option 4
S -> W : Merge PR #35
W -> W : Merge + delete branch\n+ switch to main
W -> S : "Merged! Feature is on main."

== Option 5: Tag Release (on deadline) ==

S -> W : Option 5
S -> W : R2
W -> W : git tag + push
W -> S : "Tag R2 created!"
@enduml
